# lan-guard trusted-SSID allowlist — TEMPLATE.
#
# Copy this file to `.lan-allow` (which is gitignored) and list the Wi-Fi SSIDs
# on which you permit a dev server to bind all interfaces (--host / 0.0.0.0):
#
#     cp .lan-allow.example .lan-allow
#
# One SSID per line. Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored. Match
# is exact (case- and space-sensitive). On any SSID NOT listed here — and on
# wired / Wi-Fi-off / undetectable networks — `scripts/lan-guard.sh` refuses to
# run the wrapped command (fail-closed).
#
# SSIDs are network identifiers: keep them in the gitignored `.lan-allow`, never
# in this committed template. Example (delete, use your own):
#
# my-home-wifi
# my-home-wifi-5g
